# TypeScript & Performance

## TypeScript
- **Strict typing:** Avoid `any`; use `unknown` with type guards when needed
- **Type assertions:** Use sparingly; prefer proper typing; use `as unknown as T` when narrowing from generic
- **Enums:** Use `BookingStatusEnum`, `UserRoleEnum` etc. from `@/db/sqlite/enums` - not string literals for DB/API
- **Schemas:** Zod schema → `z.infer<typeof Schema>` for types; keep single source of truth

## Performance
- **Server:** Avoid N+1 queries; use `.innerJoin`/subqueries when fetching related data
- **Frontend:** Debounce search inputs; paginate large lists; virtualize if 100+ rows
- **API:** Return only needed fields; avoid over-fetching in tRPC procedures

## Error Messages
- **User-facing:** Map external errors (Square, Google) to clear messages before throwing
- **Logging:** `console.error` with context; avoid logging sensitive data (tokens, passwords)
